The results of an online food security poll have been collated.  The idea for the poll emerged at last year’s food dialogues facilitated by the Makhanda Circle of Unity Food Security Cluster. It is hoped the poll will support the cluster’s shared efforts to raise the profile of food security in Makhanda.  The anonymous participants were asked to allocate 20 points or dots across 15 possible actions, including short-, medium- and long-term options. In order of preference, below are the top seven actions out of 15: